title: WHAT OUR SUPPLIERS SAY ABOUT US
Andrew Neva - Northwest Meat Company, Chicago
field_introduction:
"I was introduced to Choco through one of my sales reps. This is the first product in our industry which is able to tie in ordering, make it easy and put it all in one place. Of all the platforms I have looked at, Choco is the most easy to use and the most customizable, which is why I went for it. I asked all my customers to use Choco because it’s so simple and makes life easy for everybody, while really cutting down on mistakes.

I like the Catalog feature because usually customers would call me and ask me to add items to their order list, but now I can ask them to just flip through my catalog on Choco where they can find what they want, add it to their order guide themselves and even discover new products."

title: SAVE TIME ON ORDER PROCESSING & ENHANCE YOUR CUSTOMERS' EXPERIENCE. AT NO EXTRA COST.
From Pandemic to Protests: How Food Businesses Nationwide Are Responding
field_introduction: These are unprecedented times. It seems like the whole world has been brought to its knees, from the rapid and destructive spread of COVID-19 to the protests in response to police brutality and the murders of Ahmaud Arbery, Breonna Taylor, and George Floyd. The food industry isn’t exempt. So as things develop, we’ve asked people working in the food industry coast to coast to share what they’re seeing in their communities, how they’ve been affected, and how they’re responding.

title: Happy Hour Is Better With…Your Parents?
field_introduction: It’s five o’clock on a Monday at my parents’ house in Dallas and I come downstairs to a lemon drop martini sitting on the kitchen island with a note from my mom: “Be careful, Chhotu,” it reads (Chhotu = my childhood nickname). “This has three ounces of vodka in it. Very boozy. Love, Ma.”

title: How I’m Making Summer Last Forever
field_introduction: Every year I dream about all the perfectly ripe tomatoes and peaches I imagine I’ll be eating come August. But when that time (i.e., right now) arrives, I have so much pent-up anticipation that I buy more than I can reasonably eat, and a few of the tomatoes and peaches inevitably end up bruised and shriveled on my kitchen counter.

title: Burning Out on America...and My “Perfect” Wellness Routine
field_introduction: On a Sunday afternoon in early March, I am nearly nude and belly down on a massage table in an airy Altbau, squirming fitfully as my alternative therapist digs the tip of her elbow into my left rhomboid muscle.

title: There’s No One Way to Make Habichuelas Guisadas—and That’s the Point
field_introduction: To my knowledge, no one in my family has ever written—or likely ever read—a recipe for habichuelas guisadas, the Puerto Rican oxblood-colored kidney beans stewed in a tomato sauce so flavorful they belie a relatively short cooking time. All of us just know how to make it.
